    <body>
        <p>If you want your <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Flare">Word or FrameMaker </MadCap:conditionalText>output to have footers (to hold content such as text and page numbers), you can accomplish this by inserting a page footer proxy into a master page. The page footer proxy lets you insert content or automatic <MadCap:keyword term="Page numbers:printed output;Print-based output:page numbers"></MadCap:keyword>page numbering (specifically designated for the first page, even pages, or odd pages) in a master page. Use the page footer proxy to insert content and page numbering below the body proxy.</p>
